BXAdesign’s Privacy Policy
BXAdesign is committed to protecting their customer’s privacy. We present this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Data we collect.
1. User Consent.
When you download and install our application, it means you agree to the terms of our Privacy Policy and you expressly allowed accessing our collection, use and disclosure of your Personal Data in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
2. Types of Data We Collect
We take anonymous data from our customer via our site and apps you installed. We also collect your personal data, such as: our customer’s name, address, telephone number, e-mail, as well as any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data.
4. Use of Your Data
We use our customer’s personal data to:
Send you a welcome e-mail when you sign up to receive a newsletter;
Send you administrative e-mail notifications (like notices of changes to our Privacy Policy);
Respond to your inquiries related to employment opportunities or other requests;
Send newsletters, surveys, offers, and other promotional materials related to our Site/Application and for other marketing purposes
Track your in-App currency, to send relevant ads to you, to save your scores, and to provide the services you request.
5. Disclosure of Your Data.
We may share your Personal Data with third party service providers (or allow them to collect such information and IP addresses): to host or provide you with the Site or App services; to conduct quality assurance testing; to facilitate creation of accounts; to provide technical support; and/or to provide other services.
6. Privacy and Copyright Protection
Our privacy policy explains how we treat our customer’s personal data and protect them privacy when use our Products. By using our Products, means our customer agree that BXAdesign can use such data in accordance with our privacy policies.
We respond to notices of alleged copyright infringement according to the process set out in the U.S. Digital Millennium Copyright Act. If you think somebody is violating your copyrights and want to notify us, you can submit notices via our email at nyoman.ip
@gmail.com
